Tema1 APD 2020

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Data handleing:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* The parameters are passed to the thread function via the _thread_params
structure described in tema1_par.c.

* Fields:
	- the thread id, number of threads for computing the start and end
	- the width and height of julia and mandelbrot images, so they are
computed only once in main.
	- the params needed for Julia and Mandelbrot iterations described
by the _params structure.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Main:
~~~~~
	* Memory for an array of _thread_params structures is allocated.
There will be one structure for each thread, so there are no race 
conditions.	
	* Threads are created and joined when done
	* Memory is freed 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Thread_Function:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	* Only thread 0 allocates memory for the Julia result. A barrier
is set so the other threads wait for this to be done
	* Computation for the Julia algorithms are run. A barrier is set
so the other threads finish their work before writing to the file
	* The result is written in the output file then memory is freed
	* Same operations are done for the Mandelbrot algorithm
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Run_Julia:
~~~~~~~~~~
	* start and end are computed so the workload is broken in chunks
for each thread 
	* computations are mande
	* a barrier is set so the threads finish their work before
converting to screen coordinates
	* new start and end for converting coordinates
	* computations are mande

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Run_Mandelbrot:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	* start and end are computed so the workload is broken in chunks
for each thread 
	* computations are mande
	* a barrier is set so the threads finish their work before
converting to screen coordinates
	* new start and end for converting coordinates
	* computations are mande
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
